Q13
Consider the following method.

        public static int mystery(ArrayList<Integer> list) {
            int sum = 0;
            for (int i = 0; i < list.size(); i++) {
                sum += list.remove(i);
            }
            return sum;
        }

Suppose nums contains [2, 4, 6, 8]. What is returned by mystery(nums)?

Q14
Consider the following code segment.

        int[][] arr = {
            {1, 2, 3},
            {4, 5, 6},
            {7, 8, 9}
        };

        int sum = 0;
        for (int r = 0; r < arr.length; r++) {
            for (int c = 0; c < arr[0].length; c++) {
                if (r < c) {
                    sum += arr[r][c];
                }
            }
        }

What is the value of sum after the code segment executes?

Q15
Consider the following class.

        public class Counter {
            private int count;

            public Counter() {
                count = 0;
            }

            public void increment() {
                count++;
            }

            public int getCount() {
                return count;
            }
        }

Consider the following code segment.

        Counter a = new Counter();
        Counter b = a;
        a.increment();
        b.increment();
        Counter c = new Counter();
        b = c;
        b.increment();

What are the values returned by a.getCount() and b.getCount(), respectively?

Q16
Consider the following method.

        public static String mystery(String str) {
            String result = "";
            for (int i = 0; i < str.length(); i++) {
                if (i % 2 == 0) {
                    result = str.substring(i, i + 1) + result;
                }
            }
            return result;
        }

What is returned by mystery("COMPUTER")?

Q17 (FRQ)
Consider the following method.

        public static int countEven(int[] arr) {
            int count = 0;
            for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
                if (arr[i] % 2 == 0) {
                    count++;
                }
            }
            return count;
        }

Write a method that returns the sum of all odd numbers in the array. Explain your logic.

