Consider the following class.

        public class Student {
            private String name;
            private int score;

            public Student(String n, int s) {
                name = n;
                score = s;
            }
        }

Write a method that takes an ArrayList<Student> and returns the average score of all students.

Q20 (FRQ)
Consider the following method.

        public static String mystery(String str) {
            String result = "";
            for (int i = 0; i < str.length(); i++) {
                if (Character.isUpperCase(str.charAt(i))) {
                    result += str.substring(i, i + 1);
                }
            }
            return result;
        }

Write a method that does the opposite: returns only lowercase letters from the string. Explain your approach.
